column12: Fire-fighting apparatus and method of fire-fighting
column13: A firefighting apparatus comprises a nozzle assembly 100 for protruding through a barrier or wall (not shown). The apparatus 100 broadly comprises a body 120, having at a proximal end 120a a handle 130 and at a distal end 120b a tip portion 140. In use, a conduit, such as a hose or lay flat hose (not shown) is coupled to the nozzle assembly 100 at the proximal end 120a, to connect to a supply of firefighting fluid, such as water, which fluid is conducted through the interior of the body 120 to the distal end 120b where it can be delivered to a fire. A sheath member 150, in the form of an axially sliding sleeve, is positioned on the body towards its distal end, at which it abuts the tip portion 140 in the configuration shown in the figure. An annular shield 160 is fixed to, and surrounds, the sleeve 150 at a location spaced from the distal end 120b. A method of firefighting using the apparatus is also disclosed.

column12: Homeowners insurance application process using geotagged photos
column13: Methods, systems, and computer readable media are disclosed for determining a homeowners insurance quote from a captured image of a dwelling. The captured image includes geotagged information, and the address of the dwelling is determined by reverse geocoding this information. An insurance premium quote may then be generated based on the reverse geocoded address and any additional risk assessment factors, such as the building characteristics. Verification of the address may also be performed by accessing one or more databases, which may store information including addresses, coordinates, and images associated with the address. The building characteristics may be retrieved from one or more of the databases to allow for quote generation with minimal user intervention. Matching properties having comparative quotes near the dwelling address may also be generated.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR SUPPLYING AIR TO EMISSION ABATEMENT DEVICE BY USE OF TURBOCHARGER
column13: An apparatus comprises a combustion engine, an emission abatement device, and a turbocharger. The emission abatement device is fluidly coupled to the engine to receive exhaust gas therefrom. The turbocharger comprises an air compressor that is fluidly coupled to the engine to supply pressurized air to the engine and that is fluidly coupled to the emission abatement device via a flow path not including any combustion section of the engine to supply pressurized air to the emission abatement device. An associated method is disclosed.

column12: ATMOSPHERIC MIRRORING AND DYNAMICALLY VARYING THREE-DIMENSIONAL ASSISTANT ADDISON INTERFACE FOR BEHAVIORAL ENVIRONMENTS
column13: Exemplary embodiments include an intelligent secure networked health messaging system configured by at least one processor to execute instructions stored in memory, the system including a data retention system and a health analytics system, the health analytics system performing asynchronous processing with a patient's computing device and the health analytics system communicatively coupled to a deep neural network, a web services layer providing access to the data retention and the health analytics system, a batching service, wherein an application server layer transmits a request to the web services layer for data, the request processed by the batching service transparently to the patient, the request processed by the batching service transparently to the patient such that the patient can continue to use a patient facing application without disruption, and the patient-facing application having an audio sensor and a computer video sensor.

column12: COMPOSICIONES Y MÉTODOS PARA TRATAR LA PSORIASIS Y LA DERMATITIS ATÓPICA UTILIZANDO PREVOTELLA HISTICOLA
column13: En el presente documento se proporcionan métodos y composiciones relacionados con las bacterias Prevotella útiles como agentes terapéuticos, por ejemplo, para el tratamiento de la psoriasis o dermatitis atópica. Reivindicación 1: Un método para tratar la psoriasis en un sujeto humano que comprende administrar por vía oral al sujeto humano una dosis de 8 ´ 10¹⁰ a 8 ´ 10¹¹ células totales de la cepa B 50329 de Prevotella histicola (n.º de referencia de NRRL B 50329) formulada en una o más cápsulas o comprimidos de recubrimiento entérico.

column12: QUARTERNARY SUBSTITUTED BLEACH ACTIVATORS
column13: Bleaching compositions, laundry and automatic dishwashing detergent compositions comprising particular quaternary-substituted bleach activators, are provided. More specifically, the invention relates to compositions which provide enhanced cleaning/bleaching benefits though the selection of quaternary-substituted bleach activators having specific leaving groups with a conjugate acid pKa above 13 and with specific ratios of the rate of perhydrolysis to the rate of hydrolysis and the rate of perhydrolysis to the rate of diacylperoxide production. Included are preferred activator compounds and methods for washing fabrics, hard surfaces, and tableware using the activators.

column12: TOPIC COMPOSITION FOR STIMULATING SALIVATION.
column13: The present invention is intended to prepare a topic composition in spray as a drug for stimulating salivation, which includes a saliva replacing agent and an anticariogenic agent of topic application in oral mucosa. The composition is useful for treating xerostomia, burning mouth syndrome (SBA), Sjögren syndrome (SS) and periodontal disease, also being used in other transitory, chronic or permanent physiological conditions, in which salivary glands dystrophy is detected, avoiding amongst other conditions, reflux, inadequate absorption of nutrients and infections, such as recurrent candidiasis and suppurative mumps.

column12: OPERATION METHOD AND DEVICE OF AIRLESS FUEL COMBUSTION BURNER OF EMISSION ABATEMENT ASSEMBLY
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To remove soot from exhaust gas, by regenerating a particulate filter, by selectively operating a pair of fuel combustion burners.

SOLUTION: An emission abatement assembly operation method operates an emission abatement assembly so as to remove the soot from the exhaust gas from an internal combustion engine, and includes a step of determining whether or not the internal combustion engine operates in a predetermined operation state, and a step (S856) of operating the fuel combustion burner so as to regenerate the particulate filter, when the internal combustion engine operates in the predetermined operation state (S854).

column12: METHOD AND DEVICE FOR MAKING EXHAUST GAS PASS THROUGH FUEL COMBUSTION BURNER OF EMISSION REDUCING ASSEMBLY
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To stabilize flame generated by a fuel combustion burner.

SOLUTION: This fuel combustion burner operating method for operating the fuel combustion burner of an emission reducing assembly comprises a step of feeding a flow of exhaust gas into a housing of the fuel combustion burner, and a step of parting the flow of the exhaust gas into (i) a combustion flow which is fed through the combustion chamber of the fuel combustion burner and (ii) a bypassing flow which bypasses around the combustion chamber of the fuel combustion burner, and is about 70% or lower of the flow of the exhaust gas.

column12: EMISSION ABATEMENT ASSEMBLY AND METHOD OF OPERATING THE SAME
column13: An emission abatement assembly (10) includes a first particulate filter (24) having a first fuel-fired burner (20) associated therewith and a second particulate filter (26) having a second fuel-fired burner (22) associated therewith. column12: Emission abatement assembly and method of operating the same
column13: The invention discloses an emission abatement assembly which removes soot from engine emissions, including a particulate filter, a first fuel-fired burner located on the upstream of the particulate filter, and a control unit configured to control the fuel-fired burner. The control unit includes (i) a processor and (ii) a memory device electrically coupled to the processor. The memory device stores a plurality of instructions. When executed by the processing unit, the instructions allow the processor: to determine whether the engine is operated under a predetermined operation condition or not, and if the engine is operated under the predetermined operation condition, to operate the fuel-fired burner to regenerate the particulate filter. A method of operating an emission abatement assembly is also disclosed.

column12: METHOD AND APPARATUS FOR CONTROLLING FUEL-FIRED BURNER OF EMISSION ABATEMENT ASSEMBLY
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To monitor operation of a fuel-fired burner.SOLUTION: A method of operating a control unit of an emission abatement assembly includes the steps of: monitoring operation of a fuel-fired burner of the emission abatement assembly and determining if predetermined conditions are present, generating an error signal if the predetermined conditions are present, and communicating the error signal to an engine control unit of an engine.

column12: CONTROL METHOD AND DEVICE OF FUEL COMBUSTION BURNER OF EMISSION ABATEMENT ASSEMBLY
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To monitor operation of a fuel combustion burner capable of adjusting a fuel quantity supplied to a burner based on a heating temperature, by confirming the heating temperature of the burner.

SOLUTION: An operation method of a control unit of an emission abatement assembly, includes a step of determining whether or not to be in a predetermined state by monitoring operation of the fuel combustion burner of the emission abatement assembly, a step (S308) of generating an error signal when put in the predetermined state, and a step (S310) of transmitting the error signal to an engine control unit of an engine.
